**The planet is a rocky world with a thin atmosphere and slightly stronger gravity than Earth. The night sky is dark and dotted with bright, colorful stars that appear larger and closer than the stars we see from Earth. Some of the stars are so bright that they faintly illuminate the landscape below. As the night progresses, the Milky Way appears in the sky, like a bright band of light stretching from horizon to horizon. Every few minutes, a bright meteorite streaks across the sky, leaving a luminous trail behind. As the alien moon rises, it illuminates the landscape below in a silvery, bluish light. The moon appears larger than what we see from Earth and has a rough, bumpy texture. As the moon rises in the sky, the faintest stars begin to fade and the sky becomes darker and quieter. In general, the landscape below is desolate and rocky, with jagged rock formations and deep ravines. There are little or no signs of life visible, except for some strange and hardy plants that grow in crevices in the rocks.** - Upscaled (Beta) by <@173655496622866433> (Open on website for full quality) (fast)
